snippet.title: Meeting Allen B.Downey and Jeff Elkner
snippet.description:
This is an "Office Hours" behind-the-scenes video at the 2015 PyCon in Montreal where I meet Allen B. Downey for the very first time.  Of course Allen is the author of the original "Think Java" which Jeff Elkner converted to the first version of "Think Python" when later was improved by Allen again.   Since then Allen has gone on to write a whole series of "Think ..." textbooks - many of which are from O'Reilly Media.  Jeff Elkner also makes an appearance in the video.

My book "Python for Informatics" book and "Programming for Everybody" course are derived from the "Think Python" book because it was released under an open and remixable license.  My believe is that the "Think Python" book is the most impactful Open Educational Resources ever.  It has many derivations and translations and insures that people around the world always have assess to a basic Python book.

http://www.greenteapress.com/thinkpython/
http://www.allendowney.com/
http://www.elkner.net/
http://www.pythonlearn.com/

snippet.title: Coursera IHTS Office Hours Gangam Style - Seoul, Korea, October 22, 2012
snippet.description:
This is a video of my Seoul Korea Office hours for my Internet History, Technology, and Security course on Coursera, https://www.coursera.org/course/insidetheinternet - three students came to office hours: Nikolay, Julie, and Choongil.  We talked for about an hour and signed their Coursera certificates.

Since we were less than a mile from the Gangnam District in Seoul and we drank Lattes that cost about $12.00, I would say that these office hours qualified as almost "living Gangam style".  If we had danced like we were riding a horse and drank our Lattes in a single gulp it would have been more obviously "Gangnam Style" :)

This was taped October 22, 2012 in Seoul Korea.
